<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: Fri 14 Sep 2007
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly
disease information 2007; 20(37) [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/wahid-prod/public.php?page=weekly_report_index&admin=0>

African horse sickness, Senegal
-------------------------------
Information received on (and dated) 12 Sep 2007, from Dr Malik Faye,
Directeur de l'Elevage, Direction de l'Elevage, Ministere de
l'Elevage, Dakar, Senegal
Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Start date: 21 May 2007
Date of confirmation of event: 11 Jun 2007
Report date: 12 Sep 2007
Date submitted to OIE: 13 Sep 2007
Reason for notification: new strain of a listed disease
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: African horse sickness virus serotype 2
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (basic), laboratory
(advanced), necropsy
Report pertains to: entire country
New outbreaks
Outbreak 1: Mbao, Dakar
Date of start of outbreak: 28 May 2007
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not submitted)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Species: Equidae
Susceptible: 18
Cases: 1
Deaths: 1
Destroyed: 0
Slaughtered: 0
Affected population: breed horses reared in a stud farm
Outbreak 2: Pikine, Dakar
Date of start of outbreak: 21 May 2007
Outbreak status Resolved: 2 Jun 2007
Epidemiological unit: farm
Species: Equidae
Susceptible: 47
Cases: 7
Deaths: 7
Destroyed: 0
Slaughtered: 0
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 2
Total animals affected
Species: Equidae
Susceptible: 65
Cases: 8
Deaths: 8
Destroyed: 0
Slaughtered: 0
Outbreak statistics
Species: Equidae
Apparent morbidity rate: 12.31 percent
Apparent mortality rate: 12.31 percent
Apparent case fatality rate: 100.00 percent
Proportion susceptible removed*: 12.31 percent
* Removed from the susceptible population either through death,
destruction, or slaughter
Epidemiology
Source of infection: vectors
Epidemiological comments
Note by the OIE Animal Health Information Department: African horse
sickness due to serotype 9 is endemic in Senegal.
Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Onderstepoort Veterinary Institute (South
Africa) (OIE Reference Laboratory)
Species: Equidae
Test: epreuve de neutralisation virale [virus neutralization test, VNT]
Test date: 11 Jun 2007
Result: positive
Species: Equidae
Test: PCR (amplification genomique en chaine par polymerase -
polymerase chain reaction)
Test date: 11 Jun 2007
Result: positive
Species: Equidae
Test: western blot
Test date: 11 Jun 2007
Result: positive
